<div class="format_text" id="comment-body-2801">
<p>For what it&#8217;s worth, I grew a hybrid sweet corn in the garden in Madison. I liked it because the ears were small in diameter (took less space putting up on the cob). Many times country friends would give us &#8220;field&#8221; corn that we mostly cut off and put up. We did grille and boil some to eat off the cob. You may not remember this but it was very good when fresh even though it was not so sweet. I tried corn one year in Clinton but just didn&#8217;t have enough room.</p>
